<header class="hero">
	<img src="assets/logo.png" class="logo">
	{{#magma-button class="install" action="scrollToAnchor" value="install"}}Install now{{/magma-button}}
	<span class="version">Version 0.1.0 beta</span>
</header>

<main>
	<div class="overview container">
		<h2>Designed for Ember.js</h2>
		<p>Magma is a bootstrap toolkit to easily create UI interfaces for Ember.js applications. </p>
		<p>It's now even easier and faster to create your pages, for all devices.</p>
		<a href="https://github.com/4lex-io/ember-magma" target="_blank">View the project on Github</a>
	</div>
	<div class="demo">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>How does it work?</h2>
			<p class="description">This toolkit contains reusable components you can assemble to build awesome things. Better than too many words, let's take a look to an example. The following form has been generated using Magma, don't hesitate to play with it! You can see the snippet of code below.</p>

			<div class="form">
				{{#magma-form-element label="First name:"}}
					{{magma-textbox name="firstname" value=exampleFirstName}}
				{{/magma-form-element}}

				{{#magma-form-element label="Last name:"}}
					{{magma-textbox name="lastname" value=exampleLastName required=true invalid=exampleLastNameIsInvalid}}
					{{#if exampleLastNameIsInvalid}}
						{{#magma-alert alert="error"}}
							Please enter your last name
						{{/magma-alert}}
					{{/if}}
				{{/magma-form-element}}

				{{#magma-form-element label="City:"}}
					{{magma-selectbox selection=exampleCity content=exampleCityOptions optionLabelPath="name" optionValuePath="value"}}
				{{/magma-form-element}}

				{{#magma-form-element}}
					{{magma-checkbox name="terms" checked=exampleTerms required=true}}
					<label class="example-label">I accept the terms and conditions</label>

					{{#magma-popover for=".example-label" on="hover" placement="right" alignment="top"}}
						You have to check this box to continue
					{{/magma-popover}}

				{{/magma-form-element}}

				{{#magma-button action="submitForm"}}
					Submit
				{{/magma-button}}

			</div>
			<div class="formResults">
				<h3>Form result:</h3>
					<pre><code class="javascript">
{
  firstName: {{exampleFirstName}},
  lastName: {{#if exampleLastNameIsInvalid}}null{{else}}{{exampleLastName}}{{/if}},
  city: {{exampleCity.value}},
  terms: {{exampleTerms}}
}
					</code></pre>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="installation container">
		<h2 data-anchor="install">Install with Ember-CLI</h2>

		<p><strong>Note:</strong> This addon has been created based on Ember 2.0. Make sure you have this version or a newer version of Ember before you install it</p>

		<p>A simple command line can make you use the addon right now. Simply run the following at the root level of your ember project:</p>
		<code>$ ember install ember-magma</code>

	</div>

	<div class="documentation container">
		<h2>Documentation</h2>

